RANK_GROUP_CHOICES = ( (1, '1-1k'), (2, '1k-5k'), (3, '5k-10k'), (4, '10k-20k'), (5, '20k-30k'), (6, '30k+'), (7, 'Not Ranked'), (max_int, 'Empty'), )
class VulnRankFilter(filters.FilterSet): rank = filters.ChoiceFilter( label="Rank Group", choices=RANK_GROUP_CHOICES, method='filter_rank', )
def filter_rank(self, queryset, name, value): if value == "1": queryset = queryset.filter( vendor_product_rank__gt=0, vendor_product_rank__lte=1000, ) elif value == "2": queryset = queryset.filter( vendor_product_rank__gt=1000, vendor_product_rank__lte=5000, ) elif value == "3": queryset = queryset.filter( vendor_product_rank__gt=5000, vendor_product_rank__lte=10000, ) elif value == "4": queryset = queryset.filter( vendor_product_rank__gt=10000, vendor_product_rank__lte=20000, ) elif value == "5": queryset = queryset.filter( vendor_product_rank__gt=20000, vendor_product_rank__lte=30000, ) elif value == "6": queryset = queryset.filter( vendor_product_rank__gt=30000, ) elif value == "7": queryset = queryset.filter( vendor_product_rank=None, )
elif value == str(max_int): # Highest possible int to deonte empty and appear at end of list queryset = queryset.filter( scrapedvuln__vendor_product_rank=max_int )
